<section style="margin:0 0 32px;padding:24px;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:10px;background:var(--white)"><div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:minmax(0,1fr) auto;gap:20px;align-items:start"><div><div class="search-label">Trust and editorial transparency</div><h2 style="font-size:22px;line-height:1.2;letter-spacing:-.02em;margin-bottom:12px">Built by a trauma surgeon for real-world case logging and coding education</h2><p style="color:var(--ink2);margin-bottom:10px">FreeCPTCodeFinder.com was created by Graydon Stallard, DO, FACOS, FACS, a board-certified general surgeon and surgical critical care surgeon. He built it to help medical students, residents, fellows, APPs, and early-career clinicians find CPT codes faster, understand the coding logic behind them, and verify what they use against official sources.</p><p style="color:var(--ink2);margin-bottom:0">Educational reference only. Always verify CPT, CMS, payer, and program-specific requirements before submitting claims or logging cases.</p><div class="quick-links" style="margin-top:16px"><a class="quick-link" href="/authors/graydon-stallard-do.html">About the Founder</a><a class="quick-link" href="/editorial-policy.html">Editorial Policy</a><a class="quick-link" href="/contact.html">Contact / Corrections</a></div></div><img src="/assets/images/graydon-stallard-do-facos-facs.png" alt="Graydon Stallard, DO, FACOS, FACS" style="width:96px;height:96px;border-radius:12px;object-fit:cover;border:1px solid var(--line)" onerror="this.style.display='none'"></div></section><div class="search-wrap">
